# Keep `az acr build` upload size small.
# These directories are huge build artifacts that the Dockerfiles do not need
# (api/Dockerfile installs deps from pyproject.toml + uv.lock via the
# astral-sh/uv builder image; web/Dockerfile runs `npm ci` inside its build
# image).
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/.git
**/.gitignore
**/.venv
.venv
.azure
.pytest_cache
.ruff_cache
.mypy_cache
**/node_modules
**/.python_packages
web/dist
web/.next
api/build
coverage
test-results
docs
legacy
# `site/` is the mkdocs build output. It can carry broken symlinks (e.g.
# `site/assets/images/social/...`) that crash `az acr build`'s upload
# tarball with `[Errno 2] No such file or directory`, and the Container
# App images never read documentation.
site
*.zip
*.tgz
*.tar.gz
*.log
